caption.title: Real data and numerical simulations.
caption.p: RSV is plotted with a continuous line; influenza cases plotted with a dashed line. (A) RSV and influenza cases from SLP data. (B) RSV and influenza cases from model output. Horizontal axis is time in days; vertical axis is proportion of the population. Plot is shown after a transient time of 5000 days with arbitrary initial condition and parameters σ = 0.7, b 1 = 0.9162 and b 2 = 0.4566 and θ = 0.0001 for R 01 = 1.83 and R 02 = 2.28.
